name: Apartment in centre of Rotterdam
description:
This bright comfortable one bedroom apartment with a architectural thouch has a true cosy feeling! It comfortably fits two and is centrally located on a quiet street, near everything you need! Shops, musea, transport, dining, bars and supermarket!
Take a look at the floorplan to save money.
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in a quiet side street of the Witte de With. So you are near the restaurants, bars and pubs but you don't have the noise!
host_about:
Hi I'm Kim and I'm an architect. 
I studied at the TU in Delft. The apartment is renewed by myself. I wanted to created a place where you feel at home. It is a combined style of wood some color and comfortable warm furniture.  You are very welcome to find out yourself :)

Take a look at the floor plan between the pictures. The whole apartment is yours! To save money contact me directly via contact info at the floor plan.

name: Sunny garden apt in Kralingen/R'dam
host_about:
This apartment is my "pied a terre" in Rotterdam acquired many years ago.  Kralingen, where the apartment is located, was a village until 1895(?) and still feels like a village even though it is only 1 kilometer from the heart of Rotterdam...such as the main public library,  the main fruit and vegetable market and the Hoogstraat (Highstreet or Main St.).

The nearby streets and houses are really lovely, lovely, lovely and very quaint...  Just thinking about taking a walk within a block or two from my apartment lifts my spirits even when I am not at home in Rotterdam.    Rotterdam  is constantly changing and is a great modern city.

It would be my pleasure to give you more info on Rotterdam and the Netherlands ... just let me know what your interests are!

name: Romantic deckhouse on historic ship central R'dam
description:
Romantic overnight in the deckhouse of a historic ship.
This skipper's house is 4x5 m2 and 182 cm high.
With a seat on the roof of the deckhouse and a beautiful view.

This special and bright space is located in a quiet spot in the heart of Rotterdam in the former skipper's house of the historic ship "Veinard", which means "Bofkont".

Spending the night here will complete your Rotterdam experience, whether you came for relaxation and fun or as a business traveler.

welcome!
neighborhood_overview:
Trendy and dynamic neighbourhood 'Witte de Wihtstraat' is just around the corner.
Supermarket SPAR 5 minutes walking.
there are lots of things to do here close by.
host_about:
Dear Guests,

From the first of July 2021 Im the new owner of the ship MS Veinard in Rotterdam. 
Because for my work as fine artist and Polar expedition photographer I'm not always around. Michiel from rhBnB (Rotterdam Host BnB) is the host. If you plan to stay on the MS Veinard he will be your contact person,  receive you and can answer all your questions.

This kind of ship is called a Spits. She is build in Belgium in 1913 and 38.40 meter long and 5.04 meter wide.
From 1948 the ships name is Veinarrd, what ‘Lucky one’ means (bofkont in Dutch).

You are very welcome on the MS VEINARD surrounded by the vibrant city of Rotterdam. 

Esther

name: Meeting like-minded travelers
description: Cosy & Artsy! In hostel Ani&Haakien you find the real oldschool backpackers vibe, its definitly a place where you can meetup with like minded travelbuddy’s! You might even find yourself rubbing elbows with locals during dinners and the free tours! Located just 600m away from Rotterdam Central Station, Ani & Haakien is a short walk from Rotterdam’s most popular attractions such as Markthal and the famous Cube Houses! Check out the Hostel TOURS
neighborhood_overview: You won’t find us on a busy bar street — at Ani&Haakien you’ll get a good night’s sleep - but no worries, the young and bustling Central District area of Rotterdam with good coffee places, awesome design shops, rooftop bars, jazz and the electronic night life is just a dance away! So, forget about walking around with your heavy bag… drop it at the hostel, and let us tell you all about the cool stuff to do in Rotterdam. Hostel Ani & Haakien is the perfect hub for day trips! Just 10min to Delft / 40min to Amsterdam / 40min to Utrecht and 20min to The Hague!
host_about: We are Joyce & Danielle who run this cute small hostel in the centre of rotterdam already for 10 years :))) Both born and raised in Rotterdam and together with our superteam we love to welcome all travellers who like to get to know this awesome city!

name: Groepsverhuur Luciana en/of Catherina te Rotterdam
description:
With a maximum of 22 sleeping places per ship on the river in the heart of Rotterdam!
So not max. 16 pers.
On the cozy rustic shipping district, our boats are in the view of a super skyline, namely the "Manhattan on the Maas".
Shopping center and nightlife areas are in walking distance.
The fast water taxi comes in front of the door.
At least 4 nights rent applies around New Year's Eve.
Note! Both ships are on AN agenda.
So even if it seems to be occupied for a weekend, the 2nd ship is still available, always inquiries!
neighborhood_overview:
The historic shipping quarter is a beautiful village in Rotterdam centre.
Scenic views, lots of greenery, nice walks and going out.
host_about:
Uw gastheer was familievader en voerde als kapitein samen met vrouw en zonen de zeilrederij Vof Europe Sailing.
Ik woon nabij mijn familie op de te verhuren zeilschepen 'Luciana', 'Catherina' en 'Marie Galante' in de Veerhaven Rotterdam centrum.
Mijn favoriete reisbestemmingen zijn in Noorwegen en Portugal.
Ik heb weinig tijd voor boeken, maar lees graag reisverhalen en (maritieme)geschiedenis.
Bij slecht weer pak ik de Bios.

name: Stylish apartment on Rotte canal with roof garden
description:
The literary haven: where hearts and bookshelves collide.
This urban oasis is as vibrant as the city itself.
From the exposed brick wall to the bookfilled nooks, every corner has been curated to embody the essence of Rotterdam's creative energy.
You have the entire apartment AND the coveted roof garden all to yourselves.
Imagine waking up in a chic, thoughtfully designed living space adorned with an eclectic mix of vintage finds, contemporary art and many, many books.
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Rubroek, the hidden gem of Rotterdam that's just waiting for you to explore its delights. Get ready to immerse yourself in my neighbourhood where creativity, vintage charm and urban energy converge into a symphony of awesomeness.
As you stroll through the streets, you'll find artisinal coffee shops that rival the coolest cafes in the world. Grab a cup of meticulously brewed coffee or a unique herbal tea blend, and take a seat at a wooden table that's practically begging for your indie novel or sketchbook.
Vitage affecionados, this neighbourhood has your name written all over it. Explore thrift stores and boutiques that are filled with retro treasures waiting to be discovered.
And when the sun sets, the energy of Rubroek transforms yet again.
Imagine trendy eateries illuminated by fairy lights, bustling with laughter and conversation. Try unique fusion cuisine or savor artsanal pizza.
( list included in house manual).

neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is a chic gem set in the east of Rotterdam. With an expansive backyard, where the rest of the city is always welcome for a barbecue: the Kralingse Bos.

The east of Rotterdam boasts the city’s biggest park: the Kralingse Bos. This green oasis is a major attraction for everyone seeking to flee the busy urban streets for some fresh air and peace and quiet. Not that it’s always quiet; the Kralingse Bos is often humming with pleasant activity on sunny weekend afternoons. Nature lovers enjoy a stroll through the forest. Sun-worshipers bask on the lake’s small beach. Toddlers splash around in the wading pool or play at the petting zoo. Bigger children will love exploring the climbing park. People rollerblade, jog and cycle to their heart’s content around the lake and go sailing on the lake, while snacks are served at tables on the waterfront terraces.

name: Family / garden home at the river
description: Our spacious (175m2) light and recently renovated house (2020)  offers you best of both worlds: in the middle of nature, with the river 'de Rotte' right in front of our door, with a huge garden to enjoy the sun, but still close enough to reach the city centre by bicycle (12 min) or by foot (only 25 min). Even our Rotterdam friends envy us for this perfect spot! We rent out the house when we are out traveling ourselves, so it's fully equipped with everything you need!
neighborhood_overview: Nature and water. You'll see a lot of sports practiced here: running, biking, rowing, horse back riding. The people living here are a mix of young families and older friendly people.
host_about:
Together with my two boys, I live in one of the most beautiful parts of Rotterdam, at the river the Rotte. It always feels like holiday at home, surrounded by nature, and only 15 minutes (by bike!) from the citycentre.

We all love to travel, and meet new people. And next to traveling, photography is my passion and (lucky me!) profession. 
To combine both of these beautiful things in life makes me a real lucky and happy women! 

Before we bought this house we went traveling for 15 months all over the world, so we know that to really get to know a place, you have to meet and stay with the locals.
That is why we think AirBnB is a perfect medium, both as a guest ánd as a host!

name: Rotterdam's coolest apartment
description:
The coolest apartment... on the coolest street... in the coolest city... in the Netherlands!

The perfect base of operations for a Rotterdam city break or vacation. This very spacious, newly renovated apartment is located right in the middle of the Witte de Withstraat and is ideal for couples, families, colleagues, or any group of up to 5 people.
neighborhood_overview:
The Witte de Withstraat is a very lively street in the city center, with cultural institutions, restaurants, galleries, cool shops, and bars.
The apartment is right in the middle, across from a former school building, which is now a museum/gallery space for modern art (Tent/Witte de With).

The street is on the so-called Art Axis (Kunst-as) between the museums on the Leuvehaven and the Museum Park (Boijmans Van Beuningen, Het Nieuwe Instituut, the Natural History Museum, and the Kunsthal). The park is a short walk from the apartment. Festivals and markets are held here all year round (including the Parade, Open Air Cinema, Swan Market, Museum Night, etc.).

New in town? There's no better place from which to discover Rotterdam than from this apartment. A must see.

neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is one of the highly recommended neighborhood of Rotterdam. Biggest part of Kralingen exist of old authentic houses and apartments constructed around (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN). In Kralingen you will find a big park around 'de kralingse plas (lake)' where you can go for a drink, picknick, run or just a stroll.

- If you like to have a picknick in the park or just a walk, you are only a 5 min walk away from the Kralingse plas.
- If you don't want to cook, you will find different restaurants (Thai, Surinam, India, Italian, Chinese) around the corner of the apartment. But if you prefer to cook, the supermarket is only 1 minute away.
- Kralingen is a relative quiet neighborhood much different than the busy city centre, but still only 10 - 15 minutes away by subway or taxi.

name: Appartment in "centrum/west" (the place to be)..
description:
Luxury appartment with breakfast facilities in the heart of Rotterdam.

Located at the Heemraadssingel, the most beautiful canal in town with its wooden bridges, broadleave trees and weeping willows, you can find our well equipped appartment that can be rented for a long– or short stay.

Additionally, our appartment is available as Bed and Breakfast with good and organic food for only 25.00 euro.

The city centre is at walking distance. Bicycles are available to go about town “the Dutch way”.
neighborhood_overview:
History
In the past, members of the more wealthy middle class took up residence in our neighboring houses. Later, the monumental buildings were mainly used as offices or institutions. In the last 20 years the neighborhood is pleasently inhibited by an artistic and entrepeneurial crowd.

The former housemaid sleeping and living quarter in the semi basement was turned into a neat and comfortable appartment in 2011.

Bars, resto's and shops are available around the corner.

name: Spacious studio, near City Centre / Rotterdam CS
description:
Excellent starting point for trips in and outside the city.
Basically a one room apartment, with private bathroom (shower) and basic cooking facilities.
Located in a relatively quiet street with mostly enough (paid 9 a.m. - 11 p.m.) parking space.
A 10 minute walk from Rotterdam CS public transport hub, concerthall De Doelen, Theater De Schouwburg and the Blijdorp ZOO.
There is a roof terrace exclusively for our guests, with a 360° view of the city skyline.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbourhood was developed in the twenties and thirties of the 20th century. The street is very atmospheric with large trees and broad sidewalks, and most of the time enough parking space. On one end of the street there is a free accessable sports ground. On the other side it runs into the Heemraadssingel, a spacious area with a canal and a childrens playgroutd.
Two blocks away, the lively Middellandstraat has a multicultural atmosphere and wide range of shops, supermarkets, espressobars and lunchrooms.
host_about:
A freelance graphic and online designer, living and working In Rotterdam with Hennie and our son. 
I like the cultural offerings of the city, such as the museums, theater and cinema's.

host_about:
Mijn naam is Ditha, 35 jaar en geboren en woonachtig in Rotterdam.
Sinds 2015 ben ik trotse eigenares van dit stadsappartement op de perfecte locatie!
Met mijn partner en baby samen ga ik binnenkort verhuizen naar een buitenwijk van Rotterdam omdat dit mooie stadsappartement gewoonweg te klein is om met z'n 3en in te blijven wonen.
Omdat ik in het verleden jarenlang dit appartement heb verhuurd via o.a. Airbnb, wil ik dat nu opnieuw doen voor een tijdje.
Dit keer is mijn gehele appartement beschikbaar via Airbnb, voorheen woonde ik er zelf ook en tegelijkertijd verhuurde ik een kamer voor 2 personen.

Ik woon, werk en studeer(de) in Rotterdam.
Sinds 2015 werk ik als zelfstandig Recruiter, Relatiemanager en Sollicitatiecoach.
Wat ik erg leuk vind aan mijn werk is het dagelijks schakelen met een diversiteit aan mensen en nationaliteiten op verschillende niveaus.

Naast dat er veel tijd gaat naar mijn lieve baby (dreumes alweer), besteed ik graag tijd aan surfen, mijn familie en vrienden, muziek volleybal, hardlopen en nieuwe plekken ontdekken.
Mijn favoriete muziek is Reggae; ik kan geen dag zonder!

Voor mij is deze plek de ideale plek van wonen; midden in het centrum, alles op loop- en fietsafstand. Ik ervaar hier het ultieme stadsgevoel met nog een beetje groen om mij heen!
Mijn appartement bevindt zich op de topetage waardoor je de hele dag kunt genieten van een mooi uitzicht.
Ik hoop dat mijn gasten zich, net als wij, ultiem thuis voelen op deze plek. Hier doen wij in ieder geval ons uiterste best voor!

description:
Modern, spacious double bedroom with lots of windows, sunny mornings in a beautiful, renovated building.
Just a 7 min. metro ride to Rotterdam centre.
Public transport,taxi,supermarkets,nightshop,drugstores,market etc are right at your doorstep.
neighborhood_overview:
Visit the district of Delfshaven, located close to vibrant Rotterdam centre. In multicultural Delfshaven no one is an outsider. The people are relaxed and friendly.
Our house is situated on a lovely, little, lively square with benches, an organic shop and McDonalds next door. Around the corner left and right you will find drugstores, money exchange, teller machine, restaurants, pubs, hairdressers,internetcafe, nailstudio, fresh fishstore, butcher, a landromat and a large variety of other small stores.
In romantic, 16th century Historical Delfshaven, close to our house, you will find a small beerfactory, art studio's , a large poolcafé and various nice restaurants.
Across the street is a large supermarket (Jumbo, open from 08:00 - 21:00 seven days a week). On Thursday and Saturday there is a large market at a 5 minute walking distance from the apartment, where you can buy a variety of products. Across from the building there is an evening supermarket, open till midnight.
host_about:
In my free time i enjoy beeing with friends, going out and going to festivals. 
In the summer i love to travel with my old-timer camper and visit festivals in Europe.

name: Cute Room for Two in Amazing Historic Ship!
description: Welcome to Avontuur - the Ark for Healing, Wellbeing and Inner Growth. A historic clipper located in the heart of the city center of Rotterdam, one of the most exciting cities in the world for travelers! Avontuur is more then just a lodging space, it is an experience. An open ashramic space that offers yoga, meditation, workshops and concerts, as well as massage, coaching and an amazing spa experience. We have three beautiful spaces available, the Cute Room, the Cozy Room, and the Captains Hut.
neighborhood_overview:
You're right in the city centre. So all Rotterdam's highlights are within a 15 mins walk! Markthall, Erasmusbridge, Witte de Wittstraat, Tent, Meent, Coolsingel, Kunsthal, Lijnbaan, Booijman van Beuningen Museum, and the list goes on and on...

There is a restaurant right next door, a big super market, and other small shops in the neighbourhood.
host_about:
I am an architect, urban planner and self development trainer.

Born on the East African equator at sunrise on the first day of spring, I was raised throughout Africa, Asia and the Caribbean and have travelled to the far reaches of the world exploring different natures, cultures and spiritual teachings. 

Since 1991 I am based in the Netherlands and have taken my students of architecture and city planning to slums and natural disaster areas across the globe researching and implementing sustainable development. 

I also offer self development workshops and sessions, and run holistic retreats in the Caribbean.

My life is devoted to the betterment of the planet and its peoples. I use my mind, body and soul to support the individual and collective consciousness.

neighborhood_overview:
Rotterdam’s Central District is the gateway to the city and home to many international companies and multinationals. The area buzzes with a constant stream of people coming and going, which can make you think of New York. A hive of activity. Rotterdam Central railway station is the Central District’s new landmark.

Central railway station, Concert hall De Doelen, Theatre Stadsschouwburg and Cinema Pathé are literally around the corner on a 3 minutes walking distance.

West-Kruiskade is a long shopping street with shops representing every corner of the world, from Chinese to Surinamese shops selling everything under the sun and from Dutch butcher’s to Turkish baker’s shops. Its many multicultural restaurants and snack bars make it the ideal place to find an exotic bite to eat. The West-Kruiskade is often compared similar to the famous Zeedijk in Amsterdam.

The Museumkwartier is a dynamic area where lots of museums, art institutions and galleries are based

name: Cosy barnhouse surrounded with nature!
description:
The holiday apartment is located in an old stable.

The farm is located in the outskirts of Rotterdam in an old neighborhood called 'De Kandelaar'. Only 30 people live here and it is the perfect spot in the middle of nature between the (big) cities Rotterdam, Schiedam and Delft.

The perfect place to combine the city and nature!

Our farm is only 5km from Schiedam, 8km from Delft and 12km from Rotterdam and 30 minutes (by car) from the beach.
neighborhood_overview:
The old farmhouse is located in beautiful piece of nature in the middle of the big cities! There are only 20 houses and recently there is a delicious and cozy brasserie opened just a 5 minute walk.

It is a beautiful area for cycling and/or hiking. Also the old city of Delft is very close or the beautiful and modern center of Rotterdam. Both are easily accessible by bike.

The beach is also relatively close. In 25 minutes you drive to Hoek van Holland beach, or in 40 minutes to the boulevard of Scheveningen. Since the summer of 2023, it is also possible to take the metro from Schiedam to the beach of Hoek van Holland. You can park the bike or car near metro station "Nieuwland (Schiedam)". You get off on the boulevard in Hoek van Holland! For more information, you can visit the website of Ret or 9292ov (website or app on the phone)!
host_about: In 2016 kochten wij de boerderij over van onze (schoon) moeder Marlies (Co-Host) en starten wij onze AirBnB locatie. Arne woont al bijna zijn hele leven op de boerderij en in 2012 kwam Marieke daarbij. In 2014 voegden we hond Izzi toe en in 2017 en 2020 verwelkomden we onze dochters! Naast het vakantiehuis werken wij 4 dagen per week bij een werkgever, verbouwen en onderhouden we alles zelf en gaan we graag met onze camper op vakantie!

description:

Grocery store, restaurants and cafe's close by.

neighborhood_overview:
Blijdorp is a neighbourhood in northern Rotterdam and is part of the borough Noord. The up-town neighbourhood has around 9500 inhabitants.

The construction was between 1931 and 1940 and this part of town was not affected by the bombing of Rotterdam of May 14. This is why it has been nominated bij the municipality Rotterdam for the status of conservation area.

Blijdorp is closely associated with the Rotterdam Zoo in the same district.

name: Captain's Hut in historic city center
description: Welcome to Avontuur - the Ark for Healing, Wellbeing and Inner Growth. A historic clipper located in the heart of the city center of Rotterdam, one of the most exciting cities in the world for travelers! Avontuur is more then just a lodging space, it is an experience. An open ashramic space that offers yoga, meditation, workshops and concerts, as well as massage, coaching and an amazing spa experience. We have three beautiful spaces available, the Cute Room, the Cozy Room, and the Captains Hut.
neighborhood_overview:
You're right in the city centre. So all Rotterdam's highlights are within a 15 mins walk! Markthall, Erasmusbridge, Witte de Wittstraat, Tent, Meent, Coolsingel, Kunsthal, Lijnbaan, Booijman van Beuningen Museum, and the list goes on and on...

There is a restaurant right next door, a big super market, and other small shops in the neighbourhood.
host_about:
I am an architect, urban planner and self development trainer.

Born on the East African equator at sunrise on the first day of spring, I was raised throughout Africa, Asia and the Caribbean and have travelled to the far reaches of the world exploring different natures, cultures and spiritual teachings. 

Since 1991 I am based in the Netherlands and have taken my students of architecture and city planning to slums and natural disaster areas across the globe researching and implementing sustainable development. 

I also offer self development workshops and sessions, and run holistic retreats in the Caribbean.

My life is devoted to the betterment of the planet and its peoples. I use my mind, body and soul to support the individual and collective consciousness.

name: Loft studio
description:
Our studio is located in the famous and most vibrant street in the heart of Rotterdam, de Witte de Withstraat. Near the studio are various bars and restaurants, public transport, shopping area, supermarket,museum and much more. You’ll love my place because of the elegant and trendy interior, the city view, the location and the ambiance. My place is excellent for couples, solo adventurers and business travelers.

The studio will make you feel home away from home <3
neighborhood_overview:
Witte de Withstraat is the place to be when visiting Rotterdam. It has many restaurants that are open till late and amazing bars with seating outside. It is a two minute walk to the nearest tube station and three minute walk to the shopping district.

Furthermore it is nearby the Coolsingel which houses the Rotterdam City hall, and it's nearby the shopping boulevard of the city. If you don't like the big shops you can also visite the small boutiques on the Van Oldenbarneveldstraat, Karel Doormanstraat or de Meent.
If you have a panache for art, local products or like to buy things from local artists, entrepreneurs, hobbyist/amateurs, the Witte de Withstraat is dotted with (vintage and pop-up) shops/boutiques & galleries that sell these.

It's a 10 minute walk from:
- the newly constructed Markthal, which you really should visite to buy some local products or eat something at the venues.

Light studio appartement with sunny garden. The neighbourhood is known for it's many artists and has a very old (1800's) centre. I can provide you all the info you need when you are here.

name: CHEZ ALET, Rotterdam centrum, Delfshaven
description:
6 minutes walk is nice and quiet, historic Delfshaven.
Nice to eat and drink.
Walking routes to the center I can recommend and easily accessible by public transportation.
My apartment is, renovated, vintage decorated with views of the Schie Canal.
Layout: living room, dining room, 2 bedrooms, 1 bedroom with very good double (M-line mattress) bed, 1 bedroom with bunk bed, fully equipped kitchen, washing machine, bathroom/toilet television and a balcony.
neighborhood_overview:
Nearby are several cozy shops, restaurants, cafes and attractions.
500 meters away is historic Delfshaven, an authentic piece of Rotterdam, with, among other things, the Pilgrim's Church, where the "Pilgrims fathers" left in 1620 to the "new world". In the U.S. still a concept.
The famous sea hero Piet Hein has left his mark in this area.
In Delfshaven there are inhabited flat floors and it is known for its picturesque facades. It is also home to the city brewery de Pilgrim.
The Euromast and "The Park" are 1.5 km away from the apartment. This is a nice walk along the Schie and brings you to the New Meuse. Where the Port of Rotterdam becomes visible.
There are many tourist attractions in this area. Among others the Veerhaven, the World Museum, the Kunsthal, the Depot of Boijmans etc..
You can take the water bus to Dordrecht and Kinderdijk, take a tour of the Rotterdam harbours with the Spido and admire "Manhattan on the Meuse".
With the water
host_about:
Hallo,
Als ik thuis ben en mijn koffie drink kijk ik graag naar de vrachtschepen die voorbij varen. Dit geeft mij het gevoel in een havenstad te wonen.
Ik maak graag wandelingen door de stad en drink mijn biertje in toeristisch Delfshaven wat 5 min lopen van mijn huis ligt. 
Hier ligt veel geschiedenis van de stad. Vanuit deze plek is Rotterdam min of meer uitgebouwd. Het is daar rustig en mooi. Het lijkt een beetje op Amsterdam met zijn grachten en pakhuiswoningen.

Ik ben een creatief persoon en ben graag fysiek bezig.
In mijn B&B zul je de sfeer van creativiteit kunnen proeven.
De inrichting van heel mijn huis heb ik in de stijl van het huis wat in 1924 gebouwd is. Bovendien is het een bewuste keuze om te recycelen.

Naast mijn benb vind ik het heerlijk om in mijn tuin te tuinieren.  Ik schilder graag en maak tassen. 
Ik help anderen hun huis te reorganiseren en opknappen.
Dus u zou mij in kluskleding aan kunnen treffen ;-)

Sinds kort bezit ik een camperbusje. Ik ben daar erg blij mee en ga graag naar natuulijke campings waar het vaak mooi, rustig en vriendelijk is. Bovendien is daar qua natuur veel te beleven.

The amount of windows provide beautiful light throughout the whole house.

You will find shops, eatery's and cozy restaurants all within walking distance.
neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is traditionally known as the chiquer side of Rotterdam. Romantic villa neighbourhoods and elegant lanes dominate the cityscape here. Erasmus University Rotterdam is also located here, however, so the area is home to lots of students – and they keep Kralingen lively! Oostzeedijk boasts lots of popular pubs and restaurants where you can pick up a meal for a reasonable price. One of the oldest attractions in Kralingen is Arboretum Trompenburg. In addition to the lovely old trees here, these botanic gardens offer beautiful plants and flowers and a charming teahouse.

The biggest park in Rotterdam is nearby: the Kralingse Bos, a green oasis for everyone hoping to escape the city for a breath of fresh air and some peace and quiet. Visitors rollerblade, jog and cycle around the lake to their heart’s content. Sailboats skim across the lake, while tasty snacks are served at sidewalk cafés along the waterfront.
host_about:
Hi! My name is Renee, an energetic and positive woman, and I want to welcome you in my urban meets industry house in one of the most vibrant cities of the world. Rotterdam is my hometown and I love to tell you about my favorites local spots and the culture of Rotterdam.
I was born and raised in Rotterdam and I working in the sales department of our shipyard in Rotterdam, so I can tell you all about it!

Furthermore it is nearby the Coolsingel which houses the Rotterdam City hall, and it's nearby the shopping boulevard of the city. If you don't like the big shops you can also visite the small boutiques on the Van Oldenbarneveldstraat, Karel Doormanstraat or de Meent.
If you have a panache for art, local products or like to buy things from local artists, entrepreneurs, hobbyist/amateurs, the Witte de Withstraat is dotted with (vintage and pop-up) shops/boutiques & galleries that sell these.

description:
In a nice and quiet !!! marine harbor on the 'kop van zuid' is situated this very nice and ancient / historical barge. This private ship takes up to 8 quests.

The city centre of Rotterdam is on only 10 minutes walking distance of the ship. The harbor is very spacious and has a great atmosphere. Free parking facilities are on 5 minutes walking distance.

De 'kop van Zuid' is the up-coming neighbouhood of Rotterdam. With it's theatres and good restaurants it is nowaday's the place to be!

The harbor is situated in the very multicural and up coming neighborhood 'kop van zuid'

free carparking in 5 minut

name: Family house near Historical Delfshaven
description:
Welcome in our house (built in 2010) which is located near Rotterdam's most popular Nieuwe Binnenweg street, with its many trendy lunch spots, restaurants, bars and galleries. 15 minutes walking distance to the Museumpark. The apartment is located near to historical Delfshaven. Nice to wander around and have a coffee or beer (made at the Pelgrim brewery). The Pilgrim fathers left for the States from the Old church.
Finally, my place offers enough peace and quiet to have a good night's rest.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is lively and has a great mixture of authentic and hot spots. The Binnenweg, has a variety of shops and supermarkets amongst others an organic/biological supermarket. Here you'll find Vlaams Broodhuys which serves great breakfast, lunch and coffee. Apart form the famous roti’s, Indonesian, Dominican, Thai, African food, there are many options in vegetarian and vegan food as well. Don't miss out on the vegan cupcakes at Heavenly cupcakes!. The house is located 15 minutes walking distance from many museums and other sightseeing spots for example the “Witte de Withstraat” with café’s, restaurants, museums and art galleries.

name: Cozy Oasis in Rdam with Balcony
description: Situated right in Rdam's center, behind central station. Own entrance, equipped with classy, homy interior, which makes living here so joyful. The bedroom & balcony actually open up to the south, which means sunlight floods the whole apartment! A glass of wine on the balcony with this view is a treat! The long corridor connects the space, which makes moving around very dynamic. Rain-shower, leather couch, kingsize bed, big TV, large dining table... as the name says, we like it cozy.
neighborhood_overview:
You live in blijdoorp (translated: happy village); a lush, authentic & dynamic neighborhood behind the city center.
Here you find several restaurants, pubs, supermarkets & everything you might occasionally need. With only 10 minutes walking distance from the city centre & Rotterdam's central station, so you have all the options. You can easily jump on a train to explore other beautiful dutch cities Utrecht, Amsterdam or Den Hague, or even go to the beach at Hook van Holland...
The house opens to a beautiful view. Where there used to be a monestry garden, there is now a small neighbourhood tennis court, surrounded by big trees. If it wasn't for the tiny bit of skyline, you would almost forget that you are in the city with the biggest haven in Europe!

name: Iconic Cube House in heart of Rotterdam! Room 3
description: Welcome to the one of the most unique places in Rotterdam! Designed by Dutch architect Piet Blom, this residential complex are literally cubes, tilted over by 45 degrees. This results in buildings that look, feel and behave unlike anything you’ll find elsewhere in the world. Live it up like a local in the centre of Rotterdam.
neighborhood_overview:
Prepare to be charmed by neighborhoods full of fresh-faced bikers, exquisite architecture, and locals who may speak English better than you... ;)

You are very welcome to watch these inspiring videos, curtesy of Koen Samson, about the four seasons in Rotterdam!
Autumn - https://vimeo.com/150768299
Winter - https://vimeo.com/159932613
Spring - https://vimeo.com/171542577
Summer - https://vimeo.com/184653049

name: Centre city of Rotterdam
description: Townhouse in the center of Rotterdam (Bergpolder/Blijdorp).
neighborhood_overview: Family neighborhood in the center of rotterdam. House easily accessible by tram from Rotterdam Centraal train station. Public transportation easy to reach from the house. Tram 3 min walk. Metro a little further. City can also be reached by bicycle (1 bicycle available free of charge on request), if possible to rent bicycles, for example at the train station. Lots of shops, cafes and restaurants in the center. Recommended the Kop van Zuid with Hotel New York, and the Deliplein. De Witte de Withstraat is also nice for cafes and restaurants. For shopping including the Meent. The beautiful Blijdorp zoo is nearby. Several museums, including the Kunsthal. In addition, tourist attractions such as the cube houses and the Euromast. But don't forget the Erasmus bridge on the Meuse in the evening in the dark.

name: Authentic City App. with peaceful garden.
description:
Spacious and comfortable ground floor apartment including beautiful garden.
You will have a great stay in this characteristic over 100 years old mansion in the heart of the city only 900 meters from the central station, with lot's of cafes, terraces, galleries, restaurants and shops surrounding you.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in a very nice neighborhood behind Central Station. The station is about 900 meters walk and there you will find yourself in the hart of Rotterdam which offers the nicest cafes, restaurants, museums, galleries, shops and cinemas, the museum park with Museum Boymans and De Kunsthal, the authentic Witte the Withstraat, the Binnenweg, China Town with several small toko's is all within walking distance.

Exploring the city by electric scooter is the best way.
With the electric scooter you can go to the nearby parks such as Vroesenpark and off course a "must see" Kralingse Bos. You can go to the center or take a walk along the river Maas, cross the Erasmus bridge and go by watertaxi to different parts of the city.

With public transportation nearby you can reach all different parts of the city with their own charme and character.
Public transport is nearby with tram around the corner and a subway station within 5 minutes walk.
host_about:
Hi, my name is Harald and I live in the beautiful and upcoming city of Rotterdam. I love to travel and discover the world. But coming home after another adventure always brings a smile to my face. This is because this city is my home and my home is my sanctuary. I appreciate and enjoy it a lot and I hope you will too.
Life is short, so enjoy as much as you can!

name: Beautiful 1930’s en suite apartment in Rotterdam
description:
Welcome to my beautiful, cosy and characteristic apartment. This apartment is built in the 1930s and many of the original details are still intact such as the marble fireplaces and en suite doors leading to the bedroom.

The apartment is less than a minute's walk from the tram station Schieweg (line 125, which takes you to and from Rotterdam Central Station, the city centre and Kop van Zuid), a 10 to 15-minute walk from Rotterdam Central Station.
neighborhood_overview: Rotterdam Blijdorp / Bergpolder is a very friendly and affluent neighborhood.  Many children are raised here by young professional couples, and people are very open minded. On the corner of the street you will find your groceries, drugstore, florists and fun boutiques.  Across the street is a professional Beauty Bar where you can get a massage, solarium, or your nails done. One block away you can even get pierced or tattooed...! If I won’t welcome you personally, I will have the keys at Pleur, a concept store across of my apartment.
host_about:
Hi there!

My name is Daan, I am 29 years old and have been living in Rotterdam for the past five years. 

I love traveling to the Middle East, but my favorite city in the world is Melbourne! 

If you rent my apartment you will not only enjoy the happy spirit it carries, but also the many convenient facilities of my neighborhood. You are a 12 min walk from Rotterdam Central Station, the tram is just a footstep away and within 7 minutes you are at the Metro towards The Hague or Rotterdam South. And within three minutes you are on the highway to Amsterdam, Schiphol, Utrecht or Breda.

name: Beautyfull house, with super sweet cat.
description: The house is at the edge of a large park, in a quiet neighborhood. By bus/bike/car it is 15 min to Rotterdam Center. The rented space consists of a corner house. The ground floor is a bright living room with an open kitchen, on the first floor are two bedrooms and the bathroom, and in the attic is the third bedroom. The house has a nice front yard and sunny backyard by the water. You can swim there or take the pedal boat away. Parking is free. For rent with cat
neighborhood_overview: The house is adjacent to a large park, in the park there are several playgrounds and there is a deer camp. Within 3 minutes walking distance is a large paid playground, the entrance is 0.50 cent per person. The shopping street with various fish, meat, bread, clothes, etc., is a 4-minute bike ride away or a 15-minute walk away. Rotterdam/Den Hague airport is 5 minutes away by car. Diergaarde Blijdorp is 10 minutes away and Rotterdam Center is 15 minutes away by bus, car or bike.

Welcome in the most green, charming & historical area of the city of Rotterdam. 🌱

Kralingen (next to city center Rotterdam)
is known because of its beautifull park with lake, restaurants and authentic architecture.

We ourself are sailors, on our way to the Mediterranean , which gave us the oppertunity to share our luxurious loft.
neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is full of beautifull buildings and restaurant cuisines from all over the world.

Also it is only 7 minutes by bike from the authentic buildings of Kralingen, to the metropolitan city center of Rotterdam.

- The tram (stops 100m from loft), also availible for transport.

- Next to the loft there are two restaurants which serve amazing breakfast, lunch and diner.

- For further tips have a look in the “Book of answer” which will be provided after you make an reservation.

I love Rotterdam and this exquisite neighbourhood. I rent my charming loft as I like traveling. The surrounding is just perfect. Two blocks from the lake/forest and lots of international restaurants. The Erasmus University is very close by as well as the metro and tram.
My loft has a Dutch old & modern style as well as my garden.
Welcome to Kralingen!

name: Cozy, artistic, vintage hotspot in populair area
description:
Cozy, artistic, vintage appartement in one of the most popular (creative) neighbourhoods in Rotterdam. Hipster coffeeshops and bars around the corner (just across the street), 15 minute walk to centre, 15 minute walk to central station, 10 minute walk to famous Bird (disco, bar) and good restaurants. Bakery and grocery store around the corner.

It is my goal to make you feel comfortable, welcome and safe while staying in my appartement! I want you to have an awesome and memorable time!
neighborhood_overview: This neighbourhood is very popular because it has some great area's: a park on top of an old trainstation in the sky and an airtunnel (a must see! And a nice walk), little stores and galleries at 'de hofbogen', hipster coffeeshops, vintagestores, Vroezenpark and much more!
host_about:
Hi! 

Nice to meet you! 

My name is Gwen. I work as a freelance creative and researcher for television and documentary film. My work is my passion. I love people, cultures, art, design, journalisme and basically I really enjoy life! Sounds cheesy doesn't it .. sorry I cant help it .. I just do!

I hope my cozy and vintage-art house will give you as much inspiration and joy as it gives me. And that Rotterdam will be an experience you will always remember. 
I live in a neighbourhood that is one of the hotspots in Rotterdam. Creatives and artist live her. It's filled with nice coffeeshops (the ones with coffee! ;)) and quality restaurants. 

A few of the finest bars and discotheques are in 5 minute walking distance and the city is a 10 minute walk! Where you find even more places to party or have dinner or a drink. 

I hope my house is a place where you feel comfortable, welcome and most of all inspired. 

Hope  to see you soon!

Studio 2/2

The heritage lodges are situated in the middle of the Kralingse Bos (forest), a green oasis in the heart of the city of Rotterdam.

name: Light and cosy Apartment
description:
The apartment is very light and cosy, the interior is very new. Free parking is a few Blocks away. Or for 10€ in my street. The balcony has morning and evening sun and one room for yoga/meditation. There are quite some plants.
The neighborhood (Tarwewijk) is lively and multi-cultural and filled with dutch, turkish and polish supermarkts, second hand shops, coffeeshops and restaurants.
The museum square and Katendrecht are on 10 minutes by bike, through tunnel and by watertaxi.
neighborhood_overview:
The reason i wanted to live in this area is because it is very international. There is several bruin cafe's (dutch pubs) in the area and many different restaurants, Surinam, italian, turkish, Dutch, polish and many supermarkets.
Besides that there is a brandnew 50 m swimming pool and also a Japanese centre (Shofukan) nearby that hosts teaceremonies in their teagarden on request.
There is the huge 5 km wide Zuiderpark on 5 minutes walking.
The historical Delfshaven is on a 10 minute bikeride, through the bikingtunnel under the river that is quite an experience for most foreigners.

description:
10-15 minutes from Rotterdam Central Station this peach of a high-end apartment is located. The apartment is located in the neighbourhood Blijdorp, this authentic neighbourhood survived the 2nd world war.

* A luxury kitchen
* High-end interior living room

In the same street where my apartment is located, you'll find 'De Toko'. This 4,6 star rated local restaurant is one of my favourites. They serve Indonesian food, try the "rijsttafel" for 2 (25 Euro a person).

Other recommendations (all walking distance)
* Greek at home (take-away recommended)
* Angelo Betti for pizza bangers!
* La pizza, if you're a huge fan of small dishes and other Italian food

description: We welcome you in our modern home with your family or group of friends, located in a quiet neighborhood, only 5 minutes from metro/buses/trains, supermarkets and a big shopping mall. Rotterdam itself has much to offer but is also the perfect base to visit the cities, nature, beaches & other attractions in the area.
neighborhood_overview:
Prins Alexander is a family friendly residential area in the east of Rotterdam, between the Kralingse Bos wooded park and the Zevenhuizerplas lake and its many recreational opportunities.

Convenient: from the Prins-Alexander station, you can easily catch a train to Utrecht or get the metro to Rotterdam City Centre.

• Pietje Bell adventure playground: the ultimate outdoor play area in Prinsenland, with ponds and playground equipment.
• Nesselande beach: an expansive sandy beach stretching 800 metres along the Zevenhuizerplas.
• Alexandrium Shopping Centre: 140 shops focusing on fashion and interior decoration.
• Kralingse Bos park is popular with joggers and inline skaters. On and around the lake, you can sail, swim, or just relax in the sun beside your barbecue.

description:
A beautiful house from the 1930's with good vibes, close to the city center of Rotterdam. Located in a quiet and historical neighborhood, near highway exits and public transport.

neighborhood_overview:
Historical neighbourhood, built mainly in the 1930’s, with beautiful nature on walking distance. There are several supermarkets, bars and restaurants nearby and playgrounds for the little ones. You can also find one of Rotterdams most authentic multicultural shopping streets with local stores and restaurants at 15 minutes walking distance.

Public transport is also easy to find, which brings you quickly to the city center.

There’s paid parking in the streets but there is free parking on a ten minute walking distance.

name: Huge 300m2 river side design apartment
description:
This design apartment on the Maas quay is unique because of its location and design. Everything shows that it was renovated under the supervision of an interior architect. The 4 meter high ceilings and the enormous surface of 350m2 make this house feel very spacious.

Located in the central and historic district Delfshaven, there are many attractions within walking distance. Because the metro and tram stops are close to the house, the rest of Rotterdam is also quickly and easily accessible.
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located on the quay of the Maas river in the historical Delfshaven district. Only 20 minutes from Central Station. There are many good and cozy restaurants in this neighborhood. Within walking distance is the old marina. In the old canal houses you can now find antique and curio shops, small distilleries, restaurants and some craft beer breweries.

Because this house is close to several tram stops and a metro stop, the rest of the city is well connected by public transport. You can be at the Museumpark in 10 minutes, at the Maritime museum in 15 minutes and at the boarding point for the boat trips in about 20 minutes.

The "Nieuwe Binnenweg", known for its many nice boutique shops, is only 10 minutes by metro and the Witte de With, the entertainment street with lively bars and many restaurants, is only 12 minutes away.

description:
This appartment is from Samantha, she likes to travel a lot (probably the same as you! :) ) so when she does she rents this appartment.

host_about:
Ik Stefanie (Nederlanse, getrouwd, momenteel 57 jaar) reis meestal samen met één van mijn dochters Samantha en Brigitte (28 en 31 jaar), aangezien mijn man niet zo van culturele reizen houdt. Ik geef de voorkeur aan een betaalbare accommodatie ter plaatse boven een hotel, vanwege de huiselijke sfeer en de mogelijkheid om eventueel andere mensen te leren kennen. Ik ben geen veeleisende bewoner en zal goed met uw spullen omgaan. 

Mijn stijl van reizen is low budget, ik maak graag gebruik van hostels en dergelijke, kamperen is echter niet mijn stijl. Ik kom graag in contact met plaatselijke bewoners om te horen hoe zij hun leven ervaren en hun mening te horen over deze wereld.

In het verleden heb ik op diverse reizen naar Zuid-Afrika ook vrijwilligerswerk gedaan (samen met één van mijn dochters) in de townships van Port Elizabeth. Ik vind het belangrijk om te proberen mijn steentje bij te dragen in de leefbaarheid voor andere mensen op onze aarde 

Mijn hobby's zijn lezen, handwerken, reizen met mijn kinderen en mijn werk op de klantenservice van een energiebedrijf. 

I am Stefanie ( Netherlandish , married , currently 54 years) usually travel with one of my daughters Samantha and Brigitte (25 and 28) , as my husband does not like cultural tours . I prefer an affordable accommodation spot above a hotel, because of the homey atmosphere and the opportunity to get to know any other people. I'm not a demanding occupant and will properly handle your belongings.

My style of travel is low budget , I like to use hostels and such , camping is not my style. I like to come in contact with local residents to hear how they experience their lives and hear their views on the world.

In the past I have also volunteered on several trips to South Africa (along with one of my daughters) in the townships of Port Elizabeth. I think it's important to try to do my part in the quality of life for other people on earth

My hobbies are reading , crafts, traveling with my children and my work on the customer service of an energy company.

name: Luxurious Central Studio in Monumental Warehouse
description: The centrally located luxurious studio is in the most beautiful area of Rotterdam, the Scheepvaartkwartier, where historic sailing ships gently float on the water. The studio is in a monumental building from 1860 and completely renovated in 2020. Public transport options like tram, metro & watertaxi are 3 min away. Relax in The Park, enjoy many of the atmospheric restaurants, enjoy breathtaking views from the Euromast or stroll along the Maas River. All a few steps away!
neighborhood_overview:
The Scheepvaartkwartier is a protected cityscape. Stately mansions on classic avenues bring the rich shipping history of Rotterdam to life. A romantic location for couples, who like to be immortalized by a photograph against a picturesque backdrop. Anyone who feels like a glass of wine and a tasty dinner can go to atmospheric restaurants such as Loos, Zinc or Louise Petit. The amazing Bar Berta is just next door, where you can have the best tapas outside Spain!

You’re steps away from many of the Rotterdam highlights like the Euromast Park, the Maas River, historical Veerhaven, Erasmusbrug, Markthal and cultural destinations like the Kunsthal Museum.

The Park is a popular place to relax and picnic in the summer. Moreover, all kinds of festivals and events take place. The park is home to the Euromast, the highest observation tower in the Netherlands. A restaurant with a panoramic view of the city and harbor is located at an altitude of 100 meters.
host_about: I love meeting people, music, travelling and my home town Rotterdam. I'm an Airbnb fan from day one! Next to being an Airbnb host myself I love using it while travelling. I'm very relaxed and super-positive!

name: Beautiful big house with lake view
description:
Beautiful light house overlooking the Kralingse Park, in the lively monumental neighbourhood of Kralingen, which is full of small pubs and restaurants, only 10 minutes from the Rotterdam city center.

Kralingse Park is a recreational area with boating, playgrounds, BBQ area.

The house has 2 bedrooms on the first floor and another 2 bedrooms (which are joined) on the 3rd floor. In the souterrain are another 2 spacious bedrooms.
neighborhood_overview:
Kralingen is traditionally known as the city’s chic district. You’ll find romantic villa neighbourhoods and elegant lanes lined in town houses with beautifully manicured gardens. Many students from Erasmus University Rotterdam live here, which adds a lively note to a fairly quiet area. A number of popular pubs and restaurants are situated along Oostzeedijk and Oudedijk.

The city centre are just 10 minutes by bike, tram or subway.

The green oasis of the Kralingse Bos, is a major attraction for everyone seeking to flee the busy urban streets for some fresh air and peace and quiet. Not that it’s always quiet; the Kralingse Bos is often humming with pleasant activity on sunny weekend afternoons. Nature lovers enjoy a stroll through the forest. Sun-worshipers bask on the lake’s small beach. Toddlers splash around in the wading pool or play at the petting zoo. Bigger children will love exploring the climbing park. People rollerblade, jog and cycle to their heart’s cont

host_about:
Hey Everyone,

My background is in law enforcement and I currently work in football (soccer). During my time in North America, and occasionally in Europe, I work in film and TV.

I live a very and active healthy lifestyle and also train Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, CrossFit and travel frequently to study and train. 

I use AIRBNB a lot to travel with my boyfriend Ronald as well as he moves around a lot between Europe, North America and Australia in the horticultural industry for long durations.

I am a very easy going, happy person who is respectful, enthusiastic, friendly and polite and promise to make your visit as enjoyable as possible and/or to treat your homes with the utmost care.

I am always looking forward to using airbnb to travel and host to experience new cultures, meet new people and see the world.

name: Knus Tinyhouse in R’dam, dichtbij het centrum!
description: Very cozy and cozy cottage (Ibiza style) close to the center of Rotterdam. The cottage has all the comforts; you can just lock yourself up for a weekend to relax (we ourselves have lived there for a year with a lot of fun:), but you still want to hit the terrace, shop, sniff out culture or eat out, by bike or by metro you are in the center in no time.
neighborhood_overview:
Our place is unique in Rotterdam! Surrounded by water with lots of greenery (and lots of nice waterfowl). Every day there are a number of cozy neighbourhoods! Especially the big swans are very impressive! And there's peace! You don't feel like you're that close to Rotterdam city centre.

The Kralingse lake is 5 minutes away by bike and if you continue cycling for a minute, you can dine in downtown Kralingen with its cozy bars.

If you cycle the other way, you'll be in Kinderdijk in 20 minutes (including the pound), with all its beautiful mills!

And it remains a nice idea that you are in the bustling heart of Rotterdam by bus, tram and metro (the latter is just a minute away by bike)!!

name: Central garden apartment on a lush boulevard.
description:
Situated 3,5 min walk from Rotterdam Central is this stunning apartment in a 120 year old building with many of the original features and high living room ceilings still intact.

Facing a green and lush boulevard with water, this is your perfect tranquil home base in a bustling city. You can escape the madness on the balcony or in the large garden.

The city is full of contrast. The apartment is located in one of the finest old streets of the city. The renowned modern architecture is never far.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is one of Rotterdam’s greenest and quietest. However, it is lined with cute pubs and hip coffee places. Also, you are never far away from downtown, where there is an abundance of food, drink and art culture.

Right from the doorstep is a boulevard which can be followed for miles. To the city center, or away from it to the park.
host_about:
Hi! I am a Dutch airline pilot with knack for traveling. I’m probably booking last-minute, because when on holiday I don’t plan ahead most of the times! Most often I travel together with Lotte, my girlfriend of 7 years. We live in Rotterdam.

Love music, reading, hiking, living with intent.

We have decided it would be fun to live in a different city for a few months, and therefore we rent out our apartment to reduce our own costs of staying somewhere. There are no reviews of the apartment itself as of yet, but I have been rated highly while travelling, and mean to perpetuate this while renting out. 

If you look at the map and the pictures you can see it’s a superb apartment. We are looking forward to meeting you.

name: Luxury Loft City Living
description:
Love luxury easy living in the city center? Be at the heart of it all, this good-looking 70sqm Luxury Loft Apartment is located at the hippest street of Rotterdam 'Witte de Withstraat'.
This awesome spacious pad is fully equipped & has laundry facility at the next building.

Witte de Withstraat is minutes away for Erasmus MC, Weena Central District, Rotterdam Central, shopping street Beurs,Lijnbaan & Blaak. PLUS! Ofcourse the awesome Witte de Wit street itself.
neighborhood_overview:
Witte de Withstraat also called White Street is without a doubt the coolest most vibrant street of Rotterdam. This street is also home to the very famous bar ‘De Witte Aap’, voted ‘Best Bar in the World’ by Lonely Planet.

Never a Dull Moment
With rows & rows of only proper good food, bars, clubs, wall arts & quirky shops igniting your senses, one should only fall in love with feeling so alive here. The true city vibe beats on this street, so if you're looking to stay right at the heart of Rotterdam, this is the place to be.

description:
Our cool recently renovated fully equipped apartment in the coolest quarter of Rotterdam city center.
The apartment is perfect up to a maximum of 6 guests. Whether its business or pleasure which brings you to Rotterdam, you've found the perfect place!
In the heart of Rotterdam, in the middle of the SOHO of Rotterdam, there is something to experience at every corner. You will be able to experience the lively atmosphere with all Its cafes, terraces, boutiques, museums, galleries and restaurants.
neighborhood_overview:
Rotterdam has lots to offer: for children, young people or elderly people, in or on the water, high in the air (Euromast) or inside when it is more suitable.

In Rotterdam you will never get bored exploring the city and it's surroundings.
Rotterdam is a must-see city with lots of attractions, museums, monuments and architectural highlights to look out for.
For kids, attractions at or on the water, city or port tours for every age and interest.
Cultural highlights just a few minutes walk:
- Maritiem Museum
- Wereld Museum
- Kunsthal
- Dutch Photo Museum
- National Historic Museum
- Galleries
- Cinema

The big shopping area is just next door and you are surrounded by the finest bars and restaurants.

The nice thing about the location is that it is surrounded by the classic allure and look of the Scheepvaartkwartier while the bustling city center is easy to reach. Whether it's the Markthal, the Museumkwartier, Rotterdam Centraal, the Nieuwe Maas or the Wilhelminapier. All the hotspots are close. Stops for tram, bus, water taxi and metro are within easy walking distance. name: Bohemian apartment with garden in Rotterdam
description: Welcome to my beautiful and light bohemian home on Noordereiland. An unique space in the heart of Rotterdam . You'll be staying in my 75m2 apartment on the ground floor, including spacious modern kitchen and living room, 2 bedrooms (1x king-size bed, 1x childbed with slide ;) and a bathroom with bath and shower, sunny balcony and 50m2 garden on the south-west. And oh: my worm bin (yes, do my own composting ;).
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is based in the hart of the city on the Noordereiland, an island that lies between the Meuse, right between the three iconic Rotterdam bridges. From the window you can see the river and the big white bridge (Erasmus bridge).

The neighbourhood is a very laid back place in a city that is vibrant and urban, with very nice people (so are my neighbours :). There is little car traffic as people hardly pass the island itself to get somewhere. There is a small Spar supermarket, two coffee and lunchrooms, a pop-up restaurant and several kids playgrounds in the middle of the island.
host_about:
My name is Sabine. I am an entrepreneurial anthropologist, living & working in Rotterdam.  I started my own company in 2015: BlueCity: based in a former swimmingpool in Rotterdam (Tropicana). Its core business involves sustainability and showing what we can do with waste :-)...
And my little son Jan and I have created our own paradise in the city! 

My interests are social entrepreneurship, social innovation, surfing, circle economy, systemic thinking, more, more and ever more sports and (online) large scale interventions & sustainability.

The world is my number one country :-!  But aside from all that, I love to learn! About you, about the world and about your world!
So hope to meet you soon :-)!

host_about: We love to travel and have done so through over 80 countries mainly over land. The Meent is a popular street with shops, restaurants and the best ice shop of Rotterdam (de IJssalon).

Our house is located on one of the most popular streets of Rotterdam (de Meent). There are bars, restaurants and shops. The Market hall, Blaak, cube houses and Laurens Church are within walking distance.

Take a dive under nature in in the first bunker of Cocondo! In Hoek van Holland an old German telephone bunker has been transformed in to a holiday home for two adults and two children.

You will be staying in the nature reserve and national monument ‘Vinetaduin’. Beneath these dunes lie about 70 bunkers that originate from four layers of military history of the 20th century. The telephone bunker lies in the northern part, near the villa district and entrance to the beach.
neighborhood_overview: The town of Hoek van Holland originates from digging the Nieuwe Waterweg in 1872. In the following century, thousands of defenses were built on both banks to defend this new channel. These influences have been decisive in shaping the landscape of ‘the Hook of Holland’. Even today, the Hook is continuously subject to the influence of Rotterdam and the North Sea. If you pay close attention, you will notice this everywhere. A highlight is taking a walk along the Noorderpier or the Zandmotor at Ter heide.
host_about: Originally from Hoek van Holland and co-founder of the Cocondo concept. For the pilotbunker I will be your (online) host if you need any assistance!

name: Idyllisch Tiny House op Boerderij Driebergen
description: An idyllic "Tiny house" in the yard of an extraordinary historic farmhouse located on the Schie in Rotterdam. Wibbine Kien, owner of - and programmer for - this great place has this tiny house - the "pipowagen"  - built to give people the opportunity to enjoy the unique countryside around Rotterdam. The tiny house is located in the middle of an ancient orchard with apple, pear and walnut trees and is the perfect place to unwind.
neighborhood_overview: Overschie is a small, quiet, suburb in Rotterdam. Residents talk about “the village.” The immediate area of the farm is quiet, but should you want to look for the hustle and bustle: the dynamic center of Rotterdam with countless museums, restaurants, and clubs is 8.5 km away. Also the cities of Delft (6 km) and The Hague (14 km) are nearby.

name: Cozy apartment in historic Delfshaven, Rotterdam
description:
I love to offer you my cozy appartement in historic, multicultural area Delfshaven in Rotterdam. My house will be temporarily your house. So you don't have to share the house with me or other guests. I truly hope you will feel welcome.

Supermarkets, shops metro/bus/ tram station are at a 350-500 meter distance. Within 8 minutes by metro you are at the center of Rotterdam. It's super easy to go to different places in Rotterdam, but also to visit other places like Delft, The Hague, Amsterdam.
neighborhood_overview:
Delfshaven is a melting pot of cultures with a rich history. A picturesque medieval harbour is surrounded by lively shopping streets, trend-setting architecture and creative breeding grounds. Experience the dynamics of the water, the ships and the bridges, discover charming neighbourhood parks, cosy terraces and meet 70,000 residents of 170 nationalities.

And talking about parks. Across my apartment is a small park. Perfect place to have a picnic or a BBQ during spring- and summerdays. Every Thursday and Saturday there is a local market where you can buy fresh vegetables, fruits, fish, nuts etc.

I also live next to a school. Maybe good to realize that around 8.30 am the kids will be brought to school and that they sounds very enthusiastic so see other kids again.
host_about:
Hi there!

Welcome at my page!:)
My name is Mirjam, I'm a Dutchie, in daily life I'm a social worker. In my spare time I love to visit new places, nature, singing, a sucker for good coffee,  going out for walks,  try to play guitar ( with the emphasis on 'try'), do my best to give some love to my plants, like to cook and ofcourse... traveling!

Since I was young I already liked traveling.  I remember my family and I were traveling by campervan. Such a joy we had. I continued traveling when I got older. I've been to countries within Europe, but also outside Europe, like: the US, Indonesia, South Africa, Brazil, Curacaõ, Laoh and Thailand.  I've stayed more than a year in Thailand where I've worked on voluntary base as a counselor. 

When I travel I would like to have that feeling of 'home'. That's why I  love to host and to give my guests that feeling of 'home' as well. 

That feeling of traveling and meeting new people, makes me come alive. 
So why not meeting new people, travelers, in my city Rotterdam?

I hope to get to know you a bit as well:)

name: Renewed Private No-Smoking bedroom in Delfshaven
description: Book now for comfort & warm hospitality in our LGBTQI+ 🏳️‍🌈 friendly No-Smoking and Drugs-Free Airbnb. Located in a charming setting that seamlessly blends history & urbanization, our cozy retreat is surrounded by an array of shops, restaurants, supermarkets, bakeries and bars. Capture delightful moments as you explore the picturesque streets & enjoy the convenience of being in close proximity to downtown Rotterdam. 🏙️ Seeking relaxation or adventure? Our peaceful sanctuary awaits!
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood offers tranquil environment and has a moderate safety rating. However, it is advisable to remain vigilant against pickpocketing, especially in crowded outdoor areas and public transportation like the metro.

Historic Delfshaven . . . . . . . . . 1 minute🚶🏻‍♂️
Downtown of Delfshaven . . . 2 minute🚶🏻‍♂️
Downtown of Rotterdam . . . .7 min 🚇 or 30 min🚶🏻‍♂️

Nice pictures can be captured in the historic part of Delfshaven, which still has old remaining buildings that go back as far as the 13th century.

The main street (Schiedamseweg) has a lot to offer, supermarkets, night shops, low-range($) restaurants, "brown" cafes.

Rotterdam also offers Free Walking tours which I'd recommend if you’re interested to know more about Rotterdam, its history and its hidden gems. Offered in multiple languages and usually very quick availability.
host_about:
I am 26, gay, love traveling, and getting to know other people’s cultures with an open mind and heart. I have been hosting nearly 2 years on Airbnb now.

"Love and compassion are necessities, not luxuries. Without them, humanity cannot survive." - Dalai Lama

My hobbies/passions are: playing guitar, bikes, languages, clubbing, cooking, playing Xbox and mark as many countries and places possible on Skratch :D

neighborhood_overview: We live in the heart of the cute neighbourhood Oud-Charlois, which is a stones-throw away from the large Zuiderpark, Zuidplein with a huge indoor swimming pool, a theatre and a mall and Ahoy for concerts. We are also close to the 'Maastunnel' which is accessible for both bikes, cars and pedestrians which connects our part of Rotterdam (South) to the centre of Rotterdam. The neighbourhood is friendly and residential. We love and appreciate (after living in noisy streets) how quiet it is here!

name: Stijlvolle woning in populaire wijk Blijdorp.
description: In the popular Blijdorp district, within walking distance of the city center, Tiergaardde Blijdorp and the beloved Vroesenpark, lies this tastefully decorated house that has been recently renovated. On the 1st floor of this duplex house is the living room, which is adjacent to the open kitchen with many desired amenities. Here is also the 1st bedroom incl. bunk bed for 1 adults or 2 kids. Upstairs are the bathroom and again two bedrooms, one of which is adjacent to the beautiful roof terrace.
neighborhood_overview: Blijdorp is one of the most beautiful neighborhoods of Rottedam. The city center of Rotterdam is close by, and many other amenities are right around the corner: the beautiful swimming pool "Van Manenbad", zoo "Diergaarde Blijdorp", tennis park Blijdorp, the Vroesenpark with the "Vroesenpavilion" where you can have a nice lunch and breakfast, ice cream parlor "Di Gelato" with the most stunning ice cream making and a lot of nice cafes and restaurants with a variety of offers. In the neighborhood, you'll find old and young, from families to students and starters to retirees. In spring and summer, the neighbors meet at the Statensingel or in the Vroesenpark to barbecue or sit and have a drink along the water. Supermarkets, snack bars, old-fashioned and modern pubs, thrift stores and so on...in Blijdorp you have them all. Blijdorp is just very nice and definitely worth a visit!

name: Historisch zeilschip Luciana
description:
In the heart of Rotterdam, in the shipping district, overlooking Erasmus bridge, the Maas and the most beautiful skyline in the Netherlands, you will find this unique, cozy sailing ship.
In the summer, she is' under sail 'at sea, but in the winter, she accommodates cozy groups in her home harbor.
The water taxi has a boarding spot right next door and shops, best restaurants and nightlife are in walking distance.
We have 22 sleeping places aboard so for groups this accommodation is ideal.
neighborhood_overview:
Luciana is located in the Veerhaven in the Scheepsvaartkwartier. This romantic piece of town is a protected cityscape with stately mansions on classic avenues that continue the rich shipping history of Rotterdam. One of the most beautiful places is the Veerhaven, where historic sailing ships gently on the water. It is not only a very picturesque neighborhood with a lot of history, also if you like a glass of wine and good food you are in the right place.
The neighborhood is located in the heart of Rotterdam near many beautiful museums. Art and Culture lovers can get their heart's content in Rotterdam. But you are also great for other activities. The Euromast is really around the corner. And would you rather go shopping, visit the famous Markthal, or go out? Also this is all within walking distance!
host_about:
Ik ben Hieke en woon samen met mijn man Xander in het Friese Oudehaske (nabij Heerenveen). Samen hebben we 6 kinderen die ondertussen bijna allemaal de deur al uit zijn. We hebben er nog twee thuis wonen. 

Sinds kort zijn wij de heel erg trotse eigenaar van het prachtige historische zeilschip 'Luciana' waarmee we heerlijke avonturen hopen te gaan beleven.

Haar thuishaven is Rotterdam en daar zal zij in de wintermaanden liggen. Wijzelf zullen daar ook geregeld te vinden zijn maar uw gastheer zal meestal Pieter zijn.

Pieter Boot woont met zijn gezin nabij de te verhuren zeilschepen 'Luciana', 'Catherina' en 'Marie Galante' in de Veerhaven op zijn woon/vergaderschip de 'Schoneveld'. 
Bij een verblijf op een schip gaat veiligheid voor alles en dus is Pieter dag en nacht mobiel bereikbaar. 
En zijn levensmotto is dat wat hij in werktijd mag doen zijn hobby is! 

Voor mij geldt dat ik dol ben op water, de natuur, dieren, rust en de ruimte. Ook hou ik van (buiten) sporten; ik ben in mijn element op het water maar ook in de sneeuw of op het ijs, op de mountainbike of hikend in de natuur met mijn hond. 
En uiteraard hou ik ook van gezelligheid!! Ik hoop u dan ook te ontmoeten in Rotterdam!

Streets such as Zwaanshals and Zaagmolenkade have a great range of fashion, food and design and thanks to the many catering establishments you can discover something new every evening. From special bistros, restaurants and coffee shops to your own beer brewery: there is something for everyone. Oude Noorden has several squares where events are regularly organized, such as the Rotterdam Harvest Market on Noordplein and sports and games facilities on Johan Idaplein. The Hofbogen, full of creative entrepreneurs, is also nearby. With a roof of 1.9 km long, the Luchtpark de Hofbogen is a unique experience for lounging in the open air. You don't have to look for green for long with the proximity of the Kralingse Bos and the banks of the Rotte. The house is close to supermarkets, schools and nurseries. name: Zonnige en ruime maisonnette in kunstenaarswijk
description:
Enjoy Rotterdam in this spacious, soothing accommodation.

In this old artist district you can find my maisonette home. Rotterdam is a beautiful city and from Oud-Charlois you can easily explore the area by bike or by public transport to the city center about 20-30 minutes away. Nearby (within walking distance) you will find small studios, a working mill, petting zoo and organic lunch tents. Ahoy is an 8-minute bike ride away.
neighborhood_overview:
The former village of Charlois forms the charming historical core of the Oud-Charlois district. The neighborhood is bordered by the Nieuwe Maas in the north, the Dorpsweg to the east, the Kromme Zandweg in the south and the Waalhaven to the west.
The power of Oud-Charlois is in the characterful and green environment and in the passionate residents. Today, the neighborhood is home to over 150 artists and creative entrepreneurs.
Within walking distance, you'll find a working mill, petting zoo, organic lunch tents, and studios by local artists.
Note: the apartment is 20 minutes by bike or 25-30 minutes from the city center by public transport.

Ik werk in de kunst / cultuur sector en ben bezig met mijn Master Sociologie.

name: Charming townhouse/loft near the city center
description: A beautiful, charming, and spacious townhouse of 130m2 in the picturesque Old Charlois. The high ceilings and tall windows create a sense of space and brightness. Moreover, within 5 minutes through the Maastunnel, you find yourself on the other side of the city, enjoying the city center. If you're looking for a cozy, inviting, and roomy home to truly feel at home, feel free to get in touch
neighborhood_overview:
Oud-Charlois, a historic neighborhood in Rotterdam, exudes a unique atmosphere that reaches far into the past. This charming area, located on the south side of the Maas River, offers a mix of historical architecture, green squares, and a lively community. Within 10 minutes, you can reach the most exciting area of Rotterdam city center.

One of the special features of Oud-Charlois is the beautiful Zuiderpark, a green oasis in the heart of the neighborhood. Here, residents can enjoy relaxing walks, picnics on the grass, and various cultural events. name: Cozy family home in trendy neighbourhood
description: In this centrally located accommodation everything is within reach for you and your family or friends. Our home is cozy, practical and no nonsense.
neighborhood_overview: We adore the neighborhood we live in. It has a cosy and communal vibe, but at the same time breathes the cosmopolitanism and vibrancy of Rotterdam. On Saturdays there is a lovely organic farmer's market at Noordplein (5 minutes walk). The river 'de Rotte' is a 2 minute walk and leads you to some beautiful green spots in the city. At Zwart Janstraat (2 min walk) you find everything you need in terms of groceries, little supermarket, fresh bread, nuts, lovely Moroccan breakfasts and more. At Zwaanshals (1 min walk) you find some of the most interesting and creative stores in Rotterdam, as well as various lovely second hand clothes shops. The house is close to various cafés like Tom's coffee, Hopper, Bonza and all-day breakfast at Wolly. Restaurants are also well-represented in the neighborhood ranging from the hip and delicious middle-Eastern Mecca to Spanish tapas at Destino, Italian delicacies at Mangiare, top (and relatively cheap) pizzas from Salerno.
host_about: Belgian/Dutch couple with Zambian/Portuguese roots. Temwa is a sociologist and house father for our two small children. Temwa is a surf/skate enthousiast and loves 60s and 70s rock 'n roll. As a host he is friendly, welcoming and delicate. His partner Melissa is an anthropologist and works as assistant professor at University.

neighborhood_overview:
Lots of hospitality businesses, music venues, visual art institutes and shops, a few museums and cinemas, and the municipal theatre are all just a stone's throw away from the room. name: Apartment in Old Delfshaven
description:
Stylish 3-room apartment with a view of the windmill. Open the front door and immerse yourself directly in a unique part of Rotterdam, before easily making your way to the modern city center by metro or shared scooter. Within walking distance, you'll find cozy coffee shops, a brewery, various restaurants, and a pool café.

This allows you to explore both sides of Rotterdam: from the impressive modern architecture in the city center to the charming old warehouses in Delfshaven.
neighborhood_overview:
From this unique Airbnb location, you can step directly into the enchanting old harbor, where you can enjoy a picturesque walk along historic (residential) boats, a working windmill, and an authentic sluice gate. When hunger strikes, you have the option to savor pancakes at the windmill or indulge in the various cozy cafes in the area. From a traditional Rotterdam café like 'De Ooievaar' to an authentic Lebanese restaurant called 'Le Souq.' You can also pay a visit to a real brewery, 'De Pelgrim,' or play a game of pool at the 'Poolcafé.' In this picturesque street, there's something for everyone!

Furthermore, the proximity to public transportation and the availability of shared scooters and bikes provide you with the opportunity to easily travel to the bustling city center. This way, you can explore both sides of Rotterdam: from the impressive modern architecture in the center to the charming old warehouses in Delfshaven.
